   <text>
      <body>
         <listPlace>
            <place type="monastery" subtype="institution">
               <!-- the value in this @type is one of those in the EAE and in the google spreadsheet. value of @ subtype should remain untouched-->
               <placeName><!--primary name of the place--></placeName>
               <placeName type="alt"
                  ><!--any alternative name go each in one placeName--></placeName>
               <country> </country>
               <region/>
               <settlement><!--while the previous two elements speek for themselves, this contains specific information on the  exact location, which can be simply written up--></settlement>
               <location>
                  <!-- enter in geo the coordinates, latitude and longitude as in the below example, separated by a space. 
                     This is just a representative point. Polygons and multi area geo object can also be encoded.
                  Altitude can be stored in height
                  -->
                  <geo>39.342167 14.44875</geo>
                  <height>2312.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1300"
                     ><!--enter here a marked up description of the date of foundation of this institution--></date>
                  <desc type="foundation">
                     <!--                  Account of the foundation of the institution   
                        I leave this as an example. note that the description can be fully marked up with reference to other entities.-->
                     Accodring to local tradition, the founder was <persName corresp="PRS99999mamas"
                        >ʾabunä Mamas</persName> (from the time of <persName corresp="PRS12831AdmaS"
                        >King ʿAmdä Ṣǝyon</persName> I, r. 1314-44).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">
                     <!--                     Account of the history of the institution 
                     
                     Also this should be removed and substituted with a description of the new institution beeing registered-->
                     Gätär. According to the <ref type="work" target="LIT1231Vita">Vita of saint
                        Bä-ṣälotä Mikaʾel of Däbrä Gol</ref> (ʾAmhara), he was exiled to <placeName
                        corresp="#LOC9999Gulo">Gulo Mäkäda</placeName> and died at
                        <placeName>Gwǝdgwǝde</placeName>, which seems to have been a name of the
                     area around ʾAgärhǝse. Local tradition remembers him and confirms that his
                     burial place is in the vicinity.</ab>
                  <ab type="tabot">
                     <measure quantity="4"/>
                     Tabots of Mary, Michael, Mamas, Raphael.
                  </ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <!--                     this block contains the information about the library and can contain references to the manuscripts.-->
                     25 Mss.; 10 Mss. photographed: <ref target="ES888">AQM-001</ref> "Vita of
                        Mamas";<ref target="ES888"> AQM-002</ref> "Vita of Mamas" ...</ab>
               </note>
               <listBibl type="secondary">
                  <!--                  any related bibliography can go here following the standard project rules for bibliography-->
                  <bibl/>
               </listBibl>
            </place>
            <!--               If some relation is known, than use one relation element for each. Alter or Remove the mock example below if not needed!!-->
            <listRelation>
               <relation name="contains" active="#LOC00000sssss"
                  passive="#LOC1111sssss #LOC2222ggggg"/>
            </listRelation>
            <!--            allowed values for name are 
            contains
            nearBy
            partOf
            
            you can use the attribute @period to define the period in which such relation between two places existed.
            
            -->
         </listPlace>
